    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Cal Raleigh** (70.13) and **Geraldo Perdomo** (69.12) headline our offensive efforts as the clear primary targets. **Cal Raleigh** benefits significantly from a favorable matchup against Liberatore, where his dynamic platoon advantage and promotion to the #2 spot provide an elite ceiling. Similarly, **Geraldo Perdomo** is a priority play; despite a slight platoon drag, his leadoff placement against the high-xERA M\u00e1rquez makes him a high-efficiency engine for Runs. **Bryson Stott** (66.27) also grades out strongly, as his +13% platoon boost against Elder cements his status as a locked-in starter in our middle infield.\n\nWe are paying close attention to the wind-aided matchup against Eury P\u00e9rez, which elevates the scores for **Matt Chapman**, **Luis Arraez**, and **Jung Hoo Lee**. While **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** faces a tougher test against Gausman, his high base projection keeps him in the utility slot despite a lingering BvP concern. **Taylor Ward** represents our most interesting tactical pivot; his score of 59.22 is buoyed by a massive park factor boost (+16%), which helps offset the significant risk posed by the elite arm of Crochet. **Daulton Varsho**, meanwhile, remains on the fringe at 46.63; his value is strictly situational, as we are prioritizing his speed profile despite his poor platoon alignment against Cantillo.\n\nThe bench decision for **Jeremiah Jackson** (45.71) was the tightest call of the day. He hovered near the bottom of our active lineup threshold, but his projected efficiency fell just short of the established floor due to the brutal matchup against the high-skill arm of Crochet. We are exercising caution with **Masyn Winn** and **Wenceel Perez** as well, opting to keep them on the bench to preserve our limited game caps while waiting for more favorable conditions. We have no significant weather risks to report, but owners should monitor lineup volatility for **Taylor Ward** given the high-strikeout nature of his opposing pitcher.",
